The paper discusses the application of control engineering and information and communication technology (ICT) in production and logistics, with a focus on distributed approaches and technologies that support cooperative structures. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions several topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and software engineering (cs.SE) that are relevant to the development of cooperative autonomous entities. Finally, the paper discusses the use of holonic systems (cs.MA), which are multi-agent systems that exhibit characteristics of both autonomous agents and hierarchical organizations.
